CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 18, 1945, pg. 1, reads: "Goodbye Gas Stamps - Now that gasoline rationing has been lifted by the OPA, Miss Vivian Clayton can take those long rides to her favorite swimming pool. She visited Sam Scott's garage Wednesday, dressed for the occasion, and told him to fill 'er up, as she tears up her gas stamps.  But she'll have to take it easy, because tires are still under OPA control. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Vivian Clayton tearing up gasoline rationing stamps, and Sam "Scotty" Scott pumping gas at his station, 2414 - 2416 Centre Avenue, Hill District
